timeline.bodyText:
processServiceAnnotations used to be codegen-ed separately for services to specifically recompute the annotations in services that are created within a function (via https://github.com/ballerina-platform/ballerina-lang/blob/v2.0.0-Preview7/compiler/ballerina-lang/src/main/java/org/wso2/ballerinalang/compiler/bir/codegen/JvmInstructionGen.java#L1625).
To continue to support the same, IMO we need to do something similar.
The second annotation access in the following sample used to return {i: 202}, but now returns {i: 101}.
annotation record {int i;} x on service;

int globalInt = 101;

public function getService() returns service object {} {
    return @x {i: globalInt} service object {

    };
}

public function main() {
    typedesc<service object {}> t = typeof getService();
    var v = t.@x; // {"i":101}

    globalInt = 202;
    t = typeof getService();
    v = t.@x; // used to be {"i":202}, now {"i":101}
}
Will we be fixing this anytime soon given that it's a breaking change?

